spans.text: her sister art , To animate the verse
Supine on earth an awful figure
The hoary sire Heaven's guardian care
high to Heaven its sacred Boughs
paint the voice in magic numbers bound
the warm sun , as erst when Memnon played , Wake with his rising beam the vocal shade
Bending to hear the lay , so sweet
to speak , and lift his hand
Blessed with all man could wish , or prince
Asa , good and great , the sceptre
Asa , good and great , the sceptre
spoils , triumphant he returned , And half her swarthy sons sad Ethiopia mourned
half her swarthy sons sad Ethiopia
their fair laurels wither on thy brow
his throne , fair happiness and peace Smoothed every brow
drought incumbent on the thirsty ground , Long since had breathed her scorching blasts around
luxurious through the sucking plain ; Fresh honours the reviving fields adorn , And over the desert Plenty pours her horn
, on his arm , the royal eagle stand , Great type of conquest and supreme command ; The exulting bird distinguished triumph brings , And greets the Monarch with expanded wings
the vile King his iron sceptre bear
her latest strife , And Death's chill grasp congeals the found of life
her latest strife , And Death's chill grasp
rolls full fifteen summers over thy head
Nature her inverted course forego , The day
in ancient days foretold , When Bethel's altar
whose lamented urn , In plaintive song , all Judah's daughters mourn ; For whom sad Sion's softest Sorrow flows , And Jeremiah pours his sweet melodious woes
once the fair and great , Sits deep in dust , abandoned , desolate
The blackest comprehensive scene of woes
his meek head , and God Eternal
the anguish which He bears for Thee
his gloomy reign , And the cold clay-clad dead start into life
the splendours of the enlivened glass

And OH ! till earth , and seas , and Heaven decay , Never may that fair creation fade away ; May winds and storms those beauteous colours spare , Still may they bloom , as permanent as fair , All the vain rage of wasting time
Never may that fair creation fade away
whose Cross they paint so well
